<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_idæwun" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>idæwun</orth></form>
    <sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>отрицать</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>disclaim</q>
            </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>отпираться</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>deny</q>
            </cit></sense></sense>
    <re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dæwccag</orth></form><form
            xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>idæwccag</orth></form><sense><cit
                type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>спорный</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>disputable</q>
            </cit></sense></re>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>færsuj sæ radugaj, æma sæ fuldæretæ ǧavtoncæ idæwunmæ</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>(судья) спрашивает их по очереди, но большинство пытались отрицать (свое
                    преступление)</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>(the judge) asks them by turn, but the majority tried to deny (their crime)</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>193%l2%l</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>færsuj sæ radugaj, æma sæ fuldæretæ ǧavtoncæ idæwunmæ</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>(судья) спрашивает их по очереди, но большинство пытались отрицать (свое
                    преступление)</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>(the judge) asks them by turn, but the majority tried to deny (their crime)</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>193%l2%l</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, восходит к *%ivī-dav%i-; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>dav-</w><gloss><q>говорить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>davastan</w><gloss><q>говорить</q></gloss></mentioned>. Вряд ли
        от %idaw%i ‘обвинение’, ‘тяжба’. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ædæwagæ"
                />.%n<bibl><author>Benveniste,</author><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>LII
                13</biblScope></bibl> 13.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">May be it traces back to *%ivī-dav%i-; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>dav-</w><gloss><q>to say</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>davastan</w><gloss><q>talk</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is hardly
        from %idaw%i ‘accusation’, ‘suit’. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ædæwagæ"
                />.%n<bibl><author>Benveniste,</author><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>LII
                13</biblScope></bibl> 13.</etym>
</entry>
